Answer:
Antipattern Detected: Functional Decomposition: Using the include relationship

   Constructs Involved: Schedule Meeting (UC4), Select Date and Time (UC5), include relationship from UC4 to UC5
   Explanation: "Select Date and Time" (UC5) is an inclusion use case that is included by only one use case ("Schedule Meeting", UC4). UC5 is not associated with any actor directly — no actor interacts with it. UC5 does not include, extend, generalize, or get extended by any other use case. It represents a sub-step of scheduling a meeting (selecting a date/time) rather than a complete, independently valuable service observable to a user. This is classic functional decomposition: the behavior of "Schedule Meeting" has been artificially broken into a procedural sub-step via an include relationship, when "Select Date and Time" has no standalone value and is not reused elsewhere.
